Will Ruddick:

"Overly automated token contracts that try to manage value and behavior by formula instead of stewardship. They move numbers without reading context, often creating overload, artificial complexity and centralization rather than emergent, relational coordination.

Simple, human protocols create clarity; over-engineered tokenomics create fog. Demurrage on a voucher, much like bonding curves, proved too automated for how communities actually coordinate.

tldr; Let stewards set clear limits and seasonal relations; keep demurrage and curves as reversible tools—because simple, human protocols let complex systems self-organize without centralizing the power."

(https://willruddick.substack.com/p/tokenomic-automatons?)

